body:
@AoAGeneral the aim of the PR is to help Mammoth Tanks to break stalemate frontlines, not introduce it as a late game main tank as in TD. As of now the Mammoth Tank does neither.

For the record the turning speed of Mammoth and Heavy Tanks are virtually identical.

The Mammoth Tanks' weakness is demonstrably the speed. As for Artillery, eating tons Artillery fire in and out of combat is a good example on how the Mammoth Tank remains dormant. Its' selfhealrate doesn't factor in if it's lost regardless if you commit or not.

@anjew175 :  if you throw in too much , you might risk that people (regular players) wander off when they see that you changed the whole gameplay in 1 release ... 

"balance-changes" have to get in "bite for bite" ... jamming everything down the players throat in one release is the wrong way

is that reasonable enough for you ?
